			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Lull the first lvl spell is quite useless, but soothe works grand.  If you have never played an enchanter or bard, well then the cleric line of spells of lull seems useless, but in fact are such a major help, it's just one more thing a cleric has to burn mana on.  Sure you'll be an ok, maybe considered competent cleric if all you do is buff and heal, but that is BORING.  And soloing wise, sure we can solo, but after the low teens it's kind of hard to find an undead alone which you can use ward on.  Sure we could probably burn them all down to nothing, but in micro dungeons like Unrest, or dungeon settings like Befallen, the mobs will all go agro on you if you are just trying to whack on one of them, which presents a lot of problems for casting.  Finally, like any priest class we need the least experience to advance, one reason you will see many higher lvl clerics faster than any other class is the plain fact that they lvl faster than any other.  So to put that into prospective, if you play as much as another person don't be afraid to just cast heals and let yourself die to get them to the zone border, as you'll probably catch up and beat them in lvls almost no problem, especially compared to a hybrid, like a bard.  Finally, to use the soothe line (I say soothe, because lull 1st lvl is resisted way too much by even blues) just target the blues or greens you don't want to come running to help, and pull the mob you want out of the camp while they are all broken for the help link to fight just one.  Repeat as necessary in a multiple mob camp.  This makes it so we are useful before with soothe and buffs, and after/during combat with heals, and makes it so life isn't sooo boring.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
